  "narrative": "# Turn 18\n\n*7 commanders issued orders this turn.*\n\n## Strategic Decisions\n\n### CURATOR (artifact collector)\n\nDispatched 4 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W25, W25, W25, W19.\n\n### NOMAD (merchant)\n\nDispatched 3 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W19, W4, W19.\n\nEconomic activity: loaded cargo onto 1 fleets; commissioned 4 new ships.\n\n### PROPHET (apostle)\n\nEconomic activity: loaded cargo onto 1 fleets; unloaded at 2 destinations; commissioned 4 new ships.\n\n### REAVER (pirate)\n\nDispatched 4 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W8, W13, W26, W18.\n\nEconomic activity: commissioned 3 new ships.\n\n### SOLARIS (empire builder)\n\nDispatched 2 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W32, W2.\n\nEconomic activity: loaded cargo onto 1 fleets; unloaded at 1 destinations; commissioned 23 new ships; invested in 2 units of industry.\n\n### TERRAN (empire builder)\n\nDispatched 2 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W14, W25.\n\nEconomic activity: unloaded at 1 destinations; commissioned 3 new ships.\n\n### TRADER (merchant)\n\nDispatched 4 fleets across the galaxy \u2014 targeting worlds W19, W17, W19, W9.\n\n## Consequences\n\n### Territorial Shifts\n\n- **TRADER** seized control of W17 (previously NOMAD).\n\n- **SOLARIS** seized control of W32 (previously CURATOR).\n\n### Fleet Movements\n\n- **CURATOR** moved: F7\u2192W25, F8\u2192W25\n\n- **NOMAD** moved: F15\u2192W19, F16\u2192W4\n\n- **REAVER** repositioned 4 fleets across the sector.\n\n- **SOLARIS** moved: F1\u2192W32, F2\u2192W2\n\n- **TERRAN** moved: F13\u2192W14, F14\u2192W25\n\n- **TRADER** moved: F3\u2192W19, F4\u2192W17\n\n### Production\n\n- **NOMAD** launched 0 new ships.\n\n- **PROPHET** launched 4 new ships.\n\n- **REAVER** launched 3 new ships.\n\n- **SOLARIS** launched 12 new ships.\n\n- **TERRAN** launched 3 new ships.\n\n- **SOLARIS** built 2 industry.\n\n### Diplomacy\n\n- **CURATOR** sent a message to **SOLARIS**: *\"Alliance Proposal from CURATOR\"*\n"
